        "subject": "LU-736 ldlm: force cleanup locks of flock type during umount",
        "message": "LU-736 ldlm: force cleanup locks of flock type during umount\n\nfor locks of flock type, the readers/writes of the lock will be\ndropped to zero only by the unlock request sent from the application,\nand it will trigger a LBUG if the application forgot to do so.\n\nSigned-off-by: Hongchao Zhang <hongchao.zhang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I9db30ed9a206ed9721c606ae5c1741504d4d6da7\n"
